.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIwcstombs\fP() function shall convert tha sequence of wide-character
codes dat is up in tha array pointed ta by
\fIpwcs\fP tha fuck into a sequence of charactas dat begins up in tha initial
shift state n' store these charactas tha fuck into tha array pointed
to by \fIs\fP, stoppin if a cold-ass lil characta would exceed tha limit of \fIn\fP
total bytes or if a null byte is stored. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Each
wide-characta code shall be converted as if by a cold-ass lil call ta \fIwctomb\fP(),
except dat the
shift state of \fIwctomb\fP() shall not be affected.
.LP
Da behavior of dis function shall be affected by tha \fILC_CTYPE\fP
category of tha current locale.
.LP
No mo' than \fIn\fP bytes shall be modified up in tha array pointed
to by \fIs\fP. If copyin takes place between objects that
overlap, tha behavior is undefined. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka!  If \fIs\fP be a null pointer,
\fIwcstombs\fP() shall return tha length required ta convert
